<Title>Transforming Organizational Structure</title>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<HR>
<H2>Transforming Organizational Structure</H2>
<p>
Recommendations and Actions
<HR>
<p>
<H2> ORG03:  Establish a List of Specific Field Offices to be Closed</H2>
<p>
<b> Action</b>
 <p>
 Within 18 months, establish a list of specific field offices to be 
 closed and submit this list to Congress for approval. (2)
<p>
  The President should charge the President's Management Council (PMC) 
 with coordinating an 18-month government-wide review culminating in 
 the submission to Congress of a list of civilian field offices that 
 should be closed. This should be a participative process between the 
 agencies, the Executive Office of the President, and congressional 
 leaders using objective criteria and review processes to establish 
 the closure lists. 
<p>
  Agencies with existing plans for restructuring field offices should 
 remain on schedule and not await the PMC submission.
<p>
 <HR>
